    "His sons took over the family business and ran it until 1874.": [],
    "Over fifty years after his death, the Dutch connoisseur <a href=\"/hofstededegrootc\">Cornelis Hofstede de Groot</a> revised his work, discounting many works, and published a version in English beginning in 1907.": [],
    "<em>Works of the Most Eminent Dutch, Flemish and French Painters</em> is landmark in connoisseurship containing all the element of today's canonical art-historical monograph (Turner).": [],
    "Smith favored Dutch painters, including 33, as opposed to only four Flemish (Rubens, van Dyck, David Teniers and Gonzales Coques) and three French (Claude, Poussin and Greuze).": [
